# KCL

> [!word]
> The algebraic sum of all branch [[61-Archive/20220408104411-current|currents]] entering and leaving a [[61-Archive/20220411113840-node|Node]] is zero at all instances of time.
>
> - Total current entering one [[61-Archive/20220411113840-node|node]] equals to the total leaving
>
> $\sum I = 0$ > ![[Pasted-image-20220417163000.png|Pasted image 20220417163000]]

- KCL stands because of [[61-Archive/20220408133318-resistors-in-parallel|Resistors in Parallel]] ([[61-Archive/20220408104411-current|Current]] splits at [[61-Archive/20220411113840-node|nodes]])

## Example

![../60-Meta-Attachments/92399aa888e783403f3912fb2b3199d1.png](data:image/png;base64,) For this [[61-Archive/20220411113840-node|node]]:

$$

I_{A}=I_{B}+I_{C}+I_{D}


$$

$I_{A}+(-I_{B})+(-I_{C})+(-I_{D})=0$
